result.execSummary:
The defendant Jason James Folts was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Incident], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jason James Folts in court with attorney Jeffrey A. Schwarz.  Catelin Ringersma appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

AS TO COUNTS 1, 2, & 3 (AMENDED):    Sentencing proceeds.  Statements made by the state, defense counsel and defendant. 

Defendant sentenced to serve 1 YEAR at the HOUSE OF CORRECTION, with release privileges for employment and treatment purposes only. Credit for ZERO days time served. 

COURT STAYS sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for a period of 2 years under the supervision of Wisconsin Department of Corrections.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION: 
* Comply with the standard rules of probation/extended supervision.
* SERVE 60 DAYS "condition time" - STAYED.  If there are any violations, the stayed condition time can be used at the Probation Department's discretion.
* No "violent" contact with the victim, Henry F.
* Perform 40 hours of community service.
* Complete a domestic abuse counseling program.
* Take any and all prescribed medications and follow any treatment regimen.
* PAY DNA surcharge - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
* PAY the balance of all applicable court costs, fees, and surcharges - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

Appeal rights given.

Defendant Jason James Folts in court with attorney Jeffrey A. Schwarz.  Catelin Ringersma appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

This matter was originally scheduled for a Final Pretrial Conference today, however, the parties have now reached an agreement.
Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form tendered to the Court.

Upon State's motion and pursuant to negotiations, Court AMENDED Count 1 to three misdemeanor counts as follows:

Count 1 - Misdemeanor Batter [a class A MISDEMEANOR], contrary to Wisc. Stats. Sec. 940.19(1), 939.51(3)(a).  
Count 2 - Disorderly Conduct, Domestic Abuse [a class B MISDEMEANOR], contrary to Wisc. Stats. Sec. 947.01(1). 939.351(3)(b), 968.075(1)(a).
Count 3 - Obstructing/Resisting an Officer [a class A MISDEMEANOR], contrary to Wisc. Stats. Sec. 946.41(1), 939.51(3)(a).

AS TO COUNTS 1, 2, & 3 (AMENDED):    Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.

Parties request to adjourn the sentencing phase.
Court GRANTS request.
Case adjourned to 08-06-2014 at 8:30 AM - Br. 2, Judge Donald's Court for Sentencing Hearing.
**Court CANCELLED the 07-23-2014 at 8:30 AM Jury Trial date before Judge Donald's Court.

Defendant's same conditions of release to continue.
